data.value:
TTG Tools By Den Em (Е.Д.В.) Modded by pashok6798 (from Den Em's agreement) Source code on: GitFlic: https://gitflic.ru/project/pashok6798/ttg-tools GitHub: https://github.com/zenderovpaulo95/TTG-Tools Gitverse: https://gitverse.ru/pashok6798/TTG-tools Check all releases here: https://gitflic.ru/project/pashok6798/ttg-tools/release or here: https://github.com/zenderovpaulo95/TTG-Tools/releases (Original developer's e-mail: d3n123@rambler.ru)
Special thanks to:
- Den Em for accept to upload his source code. - Aluigi for source code of ttarchext; - Taylor Hornby for C# source code of Blowfish encryption - Gdkchan, Stella/AboodXD for swizzle method of Nintendo Switch - Daemon1 and tge for PS4 swizzle algorithm - Josh Tamely for oodle wrapper - Hajin Jang for Zlib.Wrapper - Nemiroff thanks for fixing a bug in the Font Editor. - Krisp for adding Xbox texture support and font editing with Swizzle.
List of supported games: Telltale's Texas Hold Em, Tales of Monkey Island, Sam & Max: Season One, Sam & Max: Season Two, Wallace and Gromit's Grand Adventures, CSI: Deadly Intent, Sam & Max: The Devil's Playhouse, Puzzle Agent 1, CSI: Fatal Conspiracy, Poker Night at the Inventory, Back to the Future: The Game, Strong Bad, Hector: The Badge of Carnage, Puzzle Agent 2, Jurassic Park: The Game, The Walking Dead, Poker Night 2, The Wolf Among Us, The Walking Dead Season Two, Tales from the Borderlands, Game of Thrones - A Telltale Games Series, Minecraft: Story Mode (Seasons One and Two), The Walking Dead: Michonne, Batman (Seasons One and Two), The Walking Dead: The Final Season, The Walking Dead : The Telltale Definitive Series, Sam & Max Save the World Remastered, Sam & Max Beyond Time and Space Remastered, Sam & Max The Devil's Playhouse Remastered. Maybe some games doesn't work.
=== [Version history]
v.1.14.9 (19.08.2025) + Auto(De)Packer (Packer and Unpacker) Added support for Xbox 360 texture extraction and reinsertion + Font editor: Added support for Xbox 360 font editing
v.1.14.8 (19.07.2025) + TTG Tools: Fixed the names of the games + Font editor: Removed russian messages.
v.1.14.7 (05.07.2025) + Auto(De)Packer (Packer and Unpacker) Fixed an encoding bug where Latin characters were showing up as "?" in Back To The Future: The Game on Xbox 360 and PS4. + Font editor: Added Nemiroff's fixes to the official TTG Tools build. + TTG Tools: Removed russian messages.
v.1.14.6 (24.02.2025) + Font editor: Nemiroff fixed some critical bugs in the Font Editor. (Many thanks!)
v.1.14.5 (05.01.2025) + Auto(De)Packer Minor fixes import text files.
v.1.14.4 (16.11.2024) + Archive packer: Fix packing ttarch archives with version 9 + Auto(De)Packer and Font editor: Add support ps3 textures for oldest games (not completely tested!) + Text editor: Minor fixes with progress bars + Archive packer: Minor fixes + Archive unpacker: Minor fixes. Add support search files in archive.
v.1.14.3 (19.10.2024) + Auto(De)Packer: Fix export/import langdb files + Archive packer: Add message of packed files and now tool removes duplicated files + Archive unpacker: Change unknown error message
v.1.14.2 (09.10.2024) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed export/import dlog files + Archive unpacker: Now tool sorts filtered file formats
v.1.14.1 (08.10.2024) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed export/import dlog files + Archive unpacker: Fixed selected unpack files + Font editor: Show correct chars in char column
v.1.14 (28.09.2024) + Archive packer: Replaced zlib.net wrapper to Zlib.Wrapper by Hajin Jang Added Oodle wrapper by Josh Tamely +Archive unpacker: Add first version of archive unpacker
v.1.13.2 (14.08.2024) +TTG Tools: Add support Sam & Max The Devil's Playhouse Remastered
v.1.13.1 (02.09.2023) + TTG Tools: Add in settings supported language in code pages option if you don't code page of your language
v.1.13 (14.06.2023) + TTG Tools: Add PS4 swizzle support + Auto(De)Packer: Add support array members textures (test PC version only and extraction only! Need PVRTexTool)
v.1.12 (29.04.2023) + Auto(De)Packer: Add support xbox360/ps4 versions of text (NOT TEXTURES AND FONTS!) in Back to the Future the game.
v.1.11 (18.03.2023) + Auto(De)Packer: Add option ignore empty strings.
v.1.1 (19.02.2023) - TTG Tools: Remove some parameters from settings form and add into Auto(De)Packer form. + Auto(De)Packer: Add support new method export/import text files Add possible change dialog flags in new method export/import text files. +Text editor: Add support replace strings with tsv, old method txt files and new method txt files. Add check duplicated strings in tsv/txt files.
v.1.0.13 (04.11.2022) + TTG Tools: Add support Thai ASCII encoding (need set 874 in settings form). + Auto (De)Packer: Add support checkpoint_text.prop and statsInfo_text.prop for Walking Dead original season, android version and Definitive edition.
v.1.0.12 (03.07.2022) + TTG Tools: Now if at first time launches settings form and after set up settings application relaunch as normal. + Font editor Return message about vector fonts.
v1.0.11 (28.05.2022) - TTG Tools: Removed support additional char for games Tales from the Borderlands and Game of Thrones (recommend extract your translated files with old versions and reimport this new version if your ASCII region is not 1252.) + TTG Tools/Auto (De)Packer: Add option clear messages after extract/repack files in settings form.
v.1.0.10 (09.03.2022) + Font Editor: Minor fixes for support Walking Dead: Michonne
v.1.0.9 (09.12.2021) +TTG Tools: Add encryption key "Sam & Max Beyond Time and Space Remastered" Rewrited code for export/import textures and fonts. Experimental generator/reader DDS and PVR headers. Removed Texture viewer WARNING! Unsupport array member textures in newest Telltale's games (Since Batman Season 1) and tested PC version only.
v.1.0.7 (12.04.2021) +TTG Tools: Add encryption key "Minecraft: Season two" Add texture viewer. Experimental version. Tested only DXT1 and DXT5 textures. +Auto(De)Packer: Add support Nintendo Switch swizzle. Expiremental version!
v.1.0.6 (21.02.2021) +TTG Tools: Add support "Sam & Max save the World Remastered" Add support new version "Tales from the Borderlands" +Auto (De)Packer & Archive Packer: Now it saves your selected options. Remove option with support non-normal unicode for users with windows-1252 encoding. + Archive Packer: Now progress bar doesn't freeze when tool packs archive.
v.1.0.5 (13.09.20) + TTG Tools: Removed russian messages.
v1.0.4 (09.02.19) + TTG Tools: Minor fixes + Auto(De)Packer: Return support latest games. Add support BC4 and BC5 formats (need photoshop plugin Intel Texture Works: https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/intel-texture-works-plugin) + Font Editor: Fix import/export fonts until latest game (Walking Dead: The Definitive Series).
v1.0.3 (14.12.19) + TTG Tools Minor update - Auto(De)Packer: Removed support newer games (TWD season 4 and TWD Definitive Series). This tool won't support anymore newest games.
v.1.0.2 (03.12.19) + Auto(De)Packer: Support for The Walking Dead - The Definitive Series
v.1.0.1 (27.10.18) +TTG Tools Changed design main menu +Auto(De)packer Added support extract/import vector fonts (TTF) for The Walking Dead +Font Editor Some fixes for bitmap fonts (Walking Dead: The Final Season)
v.1.0.0 (20.05.18) +Auto(De)packer Added support landb files for The Guardians of the Galaxy
v.0.9.9b (12.06.16 - 06.06.16 "Crutch version". Everything should work properly by version 1.0.0) + TTG Tools Fixed support for importing and exporting PVR textures. + Archive Packer Fixed building old archives.
v.0.9.8b (06.03.16) + TTG Tools Added support in Archive Packer and Auto(De)Packer for using keys not listed. Also changed the encryption structure of lua scripts. Experimental version. If the encryption structure in Walking Dead: Michonne turns out to be different, it will be redone. Added encryption key for The Walking Dead: Michonne. + Archive Packer Added ability to encrypt archives and lua scripts during archive building. With the zlib.net.dll library, you can compress archives for versions 3–7 in ttarch format. + Auto(De)Packer Added ability to encrypt/decrypt lua/lenc scripts. For older games, added ability to extract iOS textures in PVR format. Texture decryption method has changed. Special thanks to aluigi for the source code of his ttarchext program. Added support for exporting textures (it is recommended to import textures as done in the original. Texture modification is still poorly supported). + Font Editor Minor bug fixes. Added support for extracting textures for older iOS games in PVR format. Added experimental font auto-decryption feature.
v.0.9.7b (07.11.15) + Archive Packer Added experimental archive building feature. (Special thanks to aluigi for the ttarchext source code) + Auto(De)Packer Slight interface changes. Added experimental ttarch2 builder for games up to Minecraft and experimental ability to encrypt langdb files for Sam & Max Season 2. Added Unicode support (for Minecraft: Story Mode). + Font Editor Added Unicode support (for Minecraft: Story Mode).
v.0.9.6b (26.09.15) + Auto(De)Packer Import/export functions now split between "Before The Wolf Among Us" and "After The Wolf Among Us". Experimented with building textures for Poker Night 2. + Font Editor Restored compatibility with older Telltale Games (at least back to Sam & Max Season 1).
v.0.9.5b (02.08.15) + Auto(De)Packer Added support for exporting/importing textures for Poker Night 2. + Font Editor Added workaround for exporting/importing coordinates in TXT format. Fonts from Poker Night 1 now work (tested with that version. Older ones not tested).
v.0.9.4b (14.07.15) + Font Editor: The fonts from The Wolf Among Us, Poker Night 2, The Walking Dead: Season Two, and The Walking Dead Remastered now work again. Slight form appearance change. Partial fixes to import/export of files. If changes are made to the font, you'll be prompted to save when closing. If just opening the form, no prompts appear. Experimented with importing/exporting textures of a different format.
v.0.9.3b (04.03.15) + Auto(De)Packer: LANGDB can now be exported/imported by actual string ID. + Font Editor: Improved import of font coordinates using a new method. (Thanks to pashok6798)
v.0.9.2b (26.02.15) + Auto(De)Packer: The letter "Г" is added only for TFTB engine games when alphabet is defined. If alphabet is not set in config.xml, files are built without "Г", and a prompt is shown. "Г" is removed on export.
v.0.9.1b (21.02.15) + Auto(De)Packer: Added support for importing textures from TFTB and GOT.
v.0.9b (20.02.15) * Continuing logs. Support for TFTB and GOT (Fonts, Textures, Text) added without full descriptions. + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed texture version switching during export. + Font Editor: Importing coordinates from another program (test). * Only TFTB and GOT font versions are currently supported.
v.0.8.9b (04.07.14) + Auto(De)Packer: More accurate parsing of TWAU textures. Probably. (Thanks to pashok6798)
v.0.8.8b (30.12.13) + Auto(De)Packer: Added texture size check during TWAU, TWD S2 texture compilation.
v.0.8.7b (23.12.13) + Auto(De)Packer: Another type of texture from The Walking Dead Season Two is extracted. Repacking textures from The Wolf Among Us and The Walking Dead Season Two works. Fixed ttarchext algorithm usage conditions (Now the tool won't try to decrypt fonts or pack found files into archives for WAU and PN2).
v.0.8.6b (18.12.13) + Auto(De)Packer: Partial extraction of textures from The Wolf Among Us.
v.0.8.5b (26.10.13) + Font Editor: For WAU fonts, missing character coordinates are now generated during import.
v.0.8.4b (15.10.13) + Font Editor: Supports WAU fonts with multiple textures. Fixed width/height mix-up for PN2 and WAU.
v.0.8.3b (14.10.13) + Auto(De)Packer: Support for The Wolf Among Us. + Font Editor: Support for The Wolf Among Us.
v.0.8.2b (10.07.13) + Font Editor: The Walking Dead works again.
v.0.8.1b (13.05.13) + Font Editor: Added ability to change width of all characters.
v.0.8.0b (13.05.13) + Font Editor: Fixed issue with Cyrillic letters being replaced by punctuation. Character coordinate copy works again. Added toggle for kerning presence (only applies to PN2 engine or newer).
v.0.7.9b (12.05.13) + Font Editor: Poker Night 2 fonts can now be edited. Other fonts may not work.
v.0.7.8 (17.01.13) + Auto(De)Packer: You can now choose whether or not to sort identical strings during export. Text from statsinfo_text.prop in The Walking Dead can be imported/exported. (seasonstatstext.prop temporarily does not work.)
v.0.7.7 (13.01.13) + Font Editor: The Walking Dead fonts now open without special tricks. + Auto(De)Packer: Optionally imports both messages and names. (Fixes developer bug in Strong Bad.)
v.0.7.6 (10.11.12) + Auto(De)Packer: Exports and imports text from seasonstatstext.prop (The Walking Dead). (May work for other .prop files too.) Fixed typos.
v.0.7.5 (10.11.12) + Auto(De)Packer: Identical lines are placed next to each other on text export.
v.0.7.4 (11.06.11) + Font Editor: Added support for Hector: Ep 1.
v.0.7.3 (20.05.11) + Auto(De)Packer: Now supports langdb import for Sam & Max 201–205. All Sam & Max 201–205 import operations now run in a thread. All threads merged for logic and simplicity. + Many small fixes.
v.0.7.2 (11.05.11) + Auto(De)Packer: DLOG files from Sam & Max 302–305 now compile properly. + Text Editor: Fixed disappearing bilingual lines during sorting. Progress bar now always reaches 100%.
v.0.7.1 (10.05.11) Many fixes and changes to Text Editor affecting import-export algorithm.
v.0.7.0 (03.05.11) + MainMenu: Hopefully fixed strange encoding in ToMI credits. Subtitle translation now works properly. Path settings now apply immediately when changed.
v.0.6.9 (31.03.11) If an error occurs while reading a txt file, a message will show the problem line. + Auto(De)Packer: On read error, a line indicating the error and file will be added. The window is now resizable.
v.0.6.8 (30.03.11) + Text Editor: Single-language import algorithm reworked. (Now it doesn't matter which file is loaded first.)
v.0.6.7 (24.03.11) Added settings window. Settings saved in XML. Disabled TextCollector (will be removed permanently). + Auto(De)Packer: Text export is now much faster. If DDS was successfully imported, it is deleted. If all DDS textures in a folder are successfully packed into D3DTX, D3DTX is deleted. If not, the faulty DDS and D3DTX remain. + MainMenu: Small GUI changes. + About: Added Twitter link and removed outdated info.
v.0.6.6 (20.03.11) + Auto(De)Packer: Restored import of files with comments in filenames.
v.0.6.5 (15.03.11) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed LANGDB export bug (introduced in previous update). Added thread completion messages (currently only for LANGDB). + Text Editor: Fixed bug when adding second file (always start with original). Added proper result save function. Translated file path no longer overwrites original path.
v.0.6.4 (14.03.11) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed bug importing textures with two specific filenames. Scroll auto-moves to end of thread output. Added message for invalid folder paths.
v.0.6.3 (03.03.11) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed string translation duplication issue.
v.0.6.2 (17.01.11) + Font Editor: Can now import coordinates from FontStudio-generated XML. Experimental support for Strong Bad. Some leftover encrypted chunks may exist. + Auto(De)Packer: Support for extracting LANGDB text. LANGDB text import/export now runs in a separate thread.
v.0.6.1 (24.12.10) Now uses less RAM. + About: Minor text fixes. + Font Editor: Error handling for unknown/encrypted font files restored. + Possibly other things, but I forgot.
v.0.6.0 (01.11.10) + Font Editor: Added support for CSI: Fatal Conspiracy. + Auto(De)Packer: LANGDB text import runs in a separate thread.
v.0.5.9 (25.10.10) Temporary button added in main menu and Text Editor creates a file with identical lines from two files.
v.0.5.8 (16.10.10) + Auto(De)Packer: d3dtx textures now built in a separate thread, now support filename comments in parentheses. Bad DDS → D3DTX build no longer crashes the app. + Text Editor: New tool — rewritten Text Collector (old one was slow and boring).
v.0.5.7 (30.09.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Texture names/extensions are now compared using ToLower().
v.0.5.6 (25.08.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Can extract DDS from unencrypted/packed D3DTX.
v.0.5.5 (19.08.10) + Font Editor: Coordinates can now be exported/imported.
v.0.5.4 (03.08.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed handling of LANGDB. Now exports text like TextCollector.
v.0.5.3 (26.07.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Paths to Input, Output, etc. now stored in external file. Fixed logic for Sam & Max Season 2.
v.0.5.2 (23.07.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Can now detect two text strings in one DLOG entry. (If three are found, contact me.)
v.0.5.1 (17.07.10) + Auto(De)Packer: Fixed a couple of annoying bugs with DLOG.
v.0.5 (17.07.10) + Auto(De)Packer: landb + txt → landb landb → txt Supports extracting and reinserting text into landb (Puzzle Agent). Fixed old bug requiring program restart. + Cleaned up code. + Main Menu: Now minimizes to tray. + Minor GUI tweaks.
v.0.4.1 (15.07.10) + AutoPacker: Can extract text from dlog into txt. (If matching txt is found in source folder, its name is used.)
v.0.4 (14.07.10) + Text Collector: More universal comment-stripping algorithm. + AutoPacker: dlog + txt → dlog Supports comments in parentheses in txt filenames. New string parsing algorithm in importer — now extremely simple.
v.0.3.6 (12.07.10) + Text Collector: Fixed bug with comment stripping inside []. It was not processed for some reason.
v.0.3.5 (07.07.10) + Text Collector: Clear fields button added, folder block disabled for now; Suggested file name is based on original with “(all)” suffix. + Font Editor: Added support for Puzzle Agent - The Mystery of Scoggins.
v.0.3 (20.06.10) + Text Collector: Merges two files into one, placing matching lines together (ignores comments, spaces, commas, etc). After editing, you can safely import this file back into the game. Works only with files containing the same number of lines.
v.0.2.1 (17.06.10) + Font Editor: when you copy coordinates, copied cell marked green; fixed rare bug with coordinates. -Known bugs: if you used a Font Editor, you need close and open program for using AutoPacker.
v.0.2 (16.06.10) + Font Editor: open, edit & save font-file (Tested: S&M Season 2-3); export/import (with recalculation of coordinates) dds from/into font. + MainMenu change ASCII code page on MainMenu (later I add normal options). + AutoPacker: encrypted font >> font (only test-version); fixed bug with uncorrect finding start of dds in font/d3dtx for encrypting. + New About + Some fixes in GUI
v.0.1 (12.06.10) + AutoPacker: dds + d3dtx >> d3dtx & (encrypted & packed d3dtx); decrypted font >> encrypted & packed font; langdb >> packed langdb. That's all... and only start!
